caption: Best meal when in Hawaii, very nice place and the creative food blew us away.
Best vegan meal of my life! Tina our sushi chef helped provide us with a amazing set of rolls that fit what we were looking for that fit our flavor spectrum! I'll definitely be back!

My only regret is that I haven’t gone sooner.  I’m glad we stumbled upon it.  The complexity and creativity in every dish had us order more and more.  Currently sitting debating if I want to order some to eat on the way home.  Congratulations on your second year!!! Hoping you have many more!
Great food, service, overall experience. Even price wise. Im not vegan (all eater), but this left wanting nothing.

Who knew that vegan sushi can be so so good. We ordered california roll, futomaki roll, spicy tofuna roll and sweet potato roll and I was blown away by how good it tasted. I am a big fan of sushi but I thought this time I will give vegan sushi a try since the reviews for this place were really good and I am glad I did. Probably one of the best vegan foods I ate from any restaurant. It came in a cute brown box which I love since there is no plastic waste.
Amazing food and service! Everything was delicious!

Wow, what can I say. Each of the roles that we tried, and there were six different ones at our table, was as good as the best sushi. The service was attentive and friendly. Would love to go there again. Now I understand why there are always lines outside.
Great vegan food.  Lentil soup good starter. Waitress was super and nice
Amazing! Was as satisfying as regular sushi if not better 🤩 awesome service, will be returning. Taking all of my friends here and would recommend!
Flavorful and thoughtfully prepared food! My friends and I will defs be back!!!

Wow what a treat to find and try the sushi! This place reminds me of Shizen from San Francisco. The sushi were super yummy. Take a look at the picture. The experience is excellent. Get a reservation to reduce wait.  My fav is def the Wedge is my favorite. Tried also Leahy, Kailua, & Sunset (comes with a burning fire which was cool)!  You really can’t go wrong. Try and be amazed!
Love this place! Best sushi I’ve ever had!
Hands down!! The best veg sushi ever..Every dish was delightful especially, The wedge special sushi roll is outstanding👏👏
Seriously.... Michelin star awardable! Bring non-vegan here, they will forever wonder: how do they do it!
Some of the best sushi you will ever have. You won't even know it's not fish!
Fabulous and elegant. The chef is outstanding and the presentation was beautiful
Wow, this place really impressed. The food tastes amazing and was beautifully presented. The staff were also very friendly and kind. Im so happy that this place is on island!
Another level to have vegan food, but still super tasty. Price is reasonable as well. Highly recommend.
Excellent. Far surpassed my expectations.   Recommended by my vegan daughter and desired by my vegan wife. Now on this carnivores' favorites list. Great!
Delicious food, gorgeous plating! We look forward to ordering again before we leave.
Sweet concept, definitely recommend the Point Reyes roll but skip the tempura and ramen. Found some dishes to be overwhelmed by sauces and the tempura batter bathing out enoki mushrooms.

This restaurant is unmatched! I couldn’t believe how amazing our meal was. The Brussels, dumplings, specialty rolls and peppers were excellent. I have missed sushi so much since going vegan so this restaurant was an amazing find. Not to mention the service was unmatched, sat and served right away. Cannot wait to come back!! Thank you

I was really impressed by Tane. My past experiences with vegan restaurants have been very boring. Tane raises the bar for what a vegan restaurant can be. Getting a reservation was challenging, which was the first good sign. Luckily walk in seeting at the sushi bar is available. Immediately on entering the restaurant you'll notice that place is trendy and upscale. The decor is well picked and arranged. The staff here are also polite and the service is prompt. They have a decent selection of beverages with cocktails, beer and wine available. Everything we saw being prepared was colorful and beautifully arranged. We ordered the Philadelphia Roll, garlic edamame, croquettes, and leahi roll. Everything was excellent. I'm not a vegan, and not a fan of vegan cream cheese but in the rolls it works well. The only change I would have made would be to add Jalapeños to the Philadelphia roll. Everything was excellent, fun, and delicious. I highly recommend this to everyone regardless of diety choices.
So many flavors! Each dish is delightful in its own way. You don't have to be vegan to enjoy this restaurant! It's amazing! My new go to :)

Great place for vegan Japanese food. Great service too. We went during a time when restaurant seating was limited due to COVID. We had 2 meals & the sushi was awesome. They have unique menu items, so don't expect a standard sushi or Japanese menu. Parking was on the street.

Incredibly delicious sushi (vegan or not) and breathtakingly beautiful. If you eat with your eyes first, you will be doubly satisfied. They even make their take out boxes gorgeous! That’s the extra mile that real sets them apart.  The customer service is equally exceptional. I had the wrong roll and they more than made up for it. I love this place!  Also the atmosphere is perfect for a romantic date or a special occasion (even if that occasion is merely eating amazing vegan sushi! 💝 ✨✨)
Delicious food, beautiful environment, and great service!
My new favorite vegan spot in Oahu...

I have had a lot of vegan sushi around the world. Tane is easily one of the best, if not the best. Many vegan sushis can start to taste the same, but I am always surprised with their creativity, playfulness and distinct flavours. A chef and an oceanographer are the owners and their bring their passion to the plate. Try the roulette. They tuck a jalapeño in one of them... at your own risk.
Amazing food and very friendly service! Their tuna substitute in the california rolls is incredible! Totally recommend all the special rolls too, explosion of flavor! 😍

You would have no idea you were eating vegan if the word wasn’t in their logo. Excellent meal. It is a rare thing to order take out and open boxes to such perfect presentations. The flavors were standout memorable. Smoke, lemon, ginger...all fresh. The ingredients that needed to be crisp were audibly so. The spices were bold but individually identifiable, which is so hard to do. I don’t know how they work this magic with vegetables, fruits, nuts and grains but it is seriously impressive.
Not even vegan but thoroughly enjoyed every dish I had while eating here. An intimate restaurant and easily some of the best sushi on island. Felt clean and friendly, good service.
It was good just wish they had more selection for the sake (like dasai of any sort)

This is an amazing place to try Japanese food for vegan or vegetarians. We loved everything we ordered. We highly recommend the Wedge for people who crave for savpury food.The service was quick and lovely.

Make a reservation!  Once your in, sit back and enjoy a fun and tasteful dinner.  I personally enjoy a steak, fried chicken and the works.  And, I have tried beyond meats, all the meat subs, and while I find some delicious...I still do not think it curbs my cravings.  With that said, I am absolutely blown away by this restaurant.  So if you are in the same boat, I absolutely still recommend this restaurant.  The bean curd nigiri was smoky, umami packed...the tomato nigiri was infused to be just the right amount of fishy in all the good ways.  The rolls were innovative, but I actually preferred the simpler, cleaner nigiri options.  The tenpura and agedashi tofu was winners as well.  Finished the dinner satisfied and full.  Made my next reservation and can't wait!
Very nice 1st time experience. Service was very friendly & helpful. Impressed with the tasty choices we selected and we're already planning our return visit!
Tasty food! Very creative with the ingredients and deco as well. A bit pricey for what it is...

I've always wanted to go to an all-vegan izakaya, and this place has more options than i could have thought or wished for. Tempura, ramen, sushi. All delicious. Great service. Make sure to reserve ahead so no surprises.

Uhmazinggggg!! The food, the people, the ambiance, the drinks! 5 stars for all. Can't wait to go back! Top roll is specialty (Ewa) and the bottom is Leahi. Loved everything we had, including butterscotch miso, bean curd nigiri, gyoza, shizen mushrooms, and matcha IPA.

Best vegan japaneese food. I always thought I don't many choice in japaneese restaurants because I am vegetarian, but here everything is my choice. We loved the food, iced tea, matcha beer & dessert. Thank you to all staff for being very friendly and smiling all the time. Chef's are the best.
Absolutely incredible.
Little pricey, but so delicious. Some of the foods taste like their meat counterpart.
Food is amazing. Staff is very friendly! I’m vegetarian trying to go vegan but the people I came here with aren’t, and this place made them think going vegan is possible while having tasty food.

ABSOLUTELY INCREDIBLE!!!! Every single detail is pure perfection. From the ambiance, to the service, to the presentation & the FLAVORS! The flavor profiles are exsquisite & everything is made with love & intention. The dishes come out fast, with no sacrifice to quality! The whole place was packed when we were there, & everything was top notch! I had such a lovely time watching them craft each dish, & after I tasted each one, I did a happy dance as my heart bursted with joy! The staff is so friendly, along with the owner, who was crafting the sushi himself, alongside another angel who also creates magical desserts daily! A+++! What a beautiful blessing! I would reccommend Tane to the entire world!
I absolutely love TVI! The food tasted great and the staff was quick and friendly. Will be back again to try more on the menu.

As a vegan, this place knocks it right out of the park. INSANELY AMAZING AND DELICIOUS VEGAN EATS. I got the Ramen, California roll, and Philadelphia roll. If you vegan and in Oahu, go to this place right now- it will be the best decision you have made!
Best sushi I've had!
Their website should say reservations are required. We walked 30 minutes to be told it was a 2 hour wait. Looks nice and would have liked to try it, but we wont go back.
Surprisingly good. It exceeded my expectations.  Everything was creative and delicious!

****HIGHLY ALOHA RECOMMENDED!****  If you’re vegan or NOT! YOU MUST TRY THIS DELICIOUS CHEF OWNED TOP SUSHI RESTAURANT!!!!  I have been here numerous times while visiting my Favorite place and nothing changes it keeps on getting better!! Thank you for having a FULLY VEGAN delicious AS EVER SUSHI RESTAURANT IN HONOLULU!!! Forever happy customer!!!  Honestly I ordered awayyyt and there wasn’t one thing I didn’t like!! YOU ARE SAFE ORDERING WHATEVER YOU WANT!!!!
We were there in January and the food is incredible. Best vegan sushi ever !! The atmosphere and staff are wonderful. Friendly and accommodating!! I wish I could give it ten stars 😍
Thoughtfully crafted and painstakingly designed, the vegan sushi is incredible. I highly recommend the eggplant nigiri and all of the special rolls at the end of the menu.
If you had asked me this morning if I wanted to eat vegan sushi, I would have said no. To my surprise, this was my best meal in Oahu.
I really enjoy the gourmet food served at this restaurant. It's not cheap but worth it!
Love this place the surprise roll was my favorite
OMG I can't believe I had never been here. The staff is on point, the food is unique and the atmosphere is nice. I have zero complaints!
Wonderful atmosphere, Great flavors, friendly staff! Exceptional sushi at an affordable price.  Must visit
High expectations were met and exceeded.

I never thought vegan sushi would be so good! I was skeptical but the chefs are astounding. The flavors are blended so perfectly and the combination of vegetable, starches, and carbs are so well balanced. You will walk out FULL. Their drinks are a treat and their seasonal desserts are a must. Even if you are not vegan, please please give this place a shot. Your taste buds will thank you. (This is vegan food done well. It doesn't take like meat and it'll never try to. It is made to stand on it's own.)
Amazing sushi.  Best I've ever had
Amazing food, several layers of flavor in every bite, great staff. Enjoyed it so much we made reservations for next week before we walked out.

Outstanding menu options from ramen to rolls (highly recommend the pacifica). Friendly, and knowledgable staff with great recommendations. Tonight was our first time, and were already planning to come back soon.
Great flavors and textures. Everything on the menu is good! The Raman is a meal in itself!!!

Wish I could give them more stars but... location is remote ( to avoid "sketchy"), food is average and it took way too long to arrive at the table. Server was nice but a little overtaken by too many tables at the same time... it's the same menu as the similar Izakaya restaurant in San Francisco... even prices are the same...

Honestly the best vegan place in town! The menu is well curated. I really enjoy the shoyu ramen and poke salad. As for rolls, the wedge, Manila Dune & Bakers are my favorites. They even have a roll called the Barber's that is a fun game to play with friends. One out of 6 rolls has a hidden ghost pepper (?) in it. Like sushi roulette, whoever unknowingly eats it will burn their mouths off and get to ake the shot in the middle. Ambiance is nice and dimly lit. The food is incredibly creative -- you won't even miss the fish when you come here. And the dessert they  offer is always changing. Service is on point and very professional. Will be back over and ova again!
Wow!!!  Honestly, this was one of the top five meals I have ever had...maybe the best!  We will definitely go back before we depart Honolulu.  Thank you for a wonderful experience!

Full disclosure: I am a vegetarian (lacto-ovo). Best vegetarian restaraunt I have ever visited, and one of the best meals I've ever had. Extraordinary experience in visiting a small plate/sushi place where I could try the food with abandon. Food was delicious.

Bad service.  From the moment I arrived the main entrance door seemed closed and the host came to let me in.  Immediately, she answered the phone to take in an order, had me waiting just to offer a seat at the bar.  What?! She proceeds to inform me that all the tables had been reserved and that the wait time is three hours.  She was incredibly indifferent and unfriendly.  That level of attitude doesn't belong in Hawaii.

Just had a lovely experience tonight.  My server, Sierra, was so well put together in appearance, hair nicely put back, as well as attentive.  I’m not sure if it’s a normal thing, but towards the end of my meal, she put down a cup of tea for me.  Comforting touch, maybe because I hadn’t ordered alcohol? Maybe because I had a slight sniffle? It was perfect.  She didn’t ask.  She just did it.  Hostess was also lovely and even the girl who filled my water.  We all know the food is amazing so I though I would touch on the service quality. Awesome.
I'm not a vegan or vegetarian and the food was exceptionally good.
Delicious food, very casual setting. Friendly service.
Amazing. Every bite was special , and by far the best sushi I have had in Hawaii . Great staff too
(Translated by Google) Excellent! Super! Saiko ni saiko!  (Original) Excellent! Super! Saiko ni saiko!

Tane was my daughters choice since she's vegan.  We ordered a variety of sushi rolls for the table and shared everything.   The flavors were complex and delicious.   The dishes were so good that we ate most of it before thinking to take pictures!  The wedge roll was probably the table favorite.   There is on street parking but there's also a parking lot just past the front door on the left side of the road.   We circled the block a few times before confirming that we could use the parking lot. If you're looking for a great vegan restaurant in Waikiki don't miss Tane!  Call ahead for reservations or you'll have to wait for a seat at the bar.

Great vibe. I love meat just as much as the next person, but the food here was exceptionally good. We ordered most of the recommended dishes and liked most of them. The food here doesn’t feel like it’s trying to pretend to not be vegan but is instead uniquely expressive of its flavors and ingredients. Not everything is a hit, but  it’s by far the best vegan restaurant I’ve been to on the island. I am a big fan of ramen, and theirs was incredibly flavorful. The dessert was also top notch.
Great Japanese food made vegan! Delicious ramen, sushi and ice cream. Reasonable pricing and nice atmosphere! Definitely recommend stopping by!
Best restaurant in Honolulu. This review is very serious.
Amazing food. Great flavors and nice ambiance.
Favorite place to go to

Love love love this place ❤️ This place was the best place I have found in this Hawaii trip 😆😆❤️ I’m so happy I found you guys and loved the staffs who were behind the counter 😍 such lovely atmosphere!! Highly recommend!
High quality, great  service, delicious food

Been here now 4 times and every single thing I've ordered was flavorful.  Avocado nigiri? I thought how are they going to make avocado and rice taste amazing, but now I can't stop ordering it haha.  Make a reservation, they seem to always be full.

I am not a vegan but I must say thier food was very flavorful and satisfying. We had shared several dishes. They also have a few specialty drinks. It's a great place to meat with friends and not to loud for conversation. Service was great and timely. Give it a try!!
Every dish we ordered  was delicious and in an amazing presentation.
Oh my goodness .. for a plant eating, gluten free family, we definitely died and went to heaven. So many wonderful flavors and you can taste the love that goes into the food. Mahalo Nui
Very Delicious! Have to try!
Absolutely delicious and wonderful service. 😊👍 must try! My favorite roll so far is called "The wedge".

Great vegan sushi, delicious and special however I must ask?  Do Vegan restaurants deserve deserve higher stars because they are plant based? Should we expect the same level of service, food quality and flavour from ethical establishments? The time limit is the deal breaker here and results in less stars. Otherwise the meal would have been 5 stars. It’s an awful experience to be rushed or to feel there is a time limit on your dining experience and for me that ruined the meal. We sat at the bar, with uncomfortable seating and very little space.  We had the Tofuna rolls, Sandy speciality roll, Mushrooms appetizer and Spicy Ramen. The Sandy was the best.  Come enjoy the Vegan sushi but for the owners please change this practice.
Delicious and amazing play on textures. Because it's all plant-based, we left feeling very light and clean, but still satiated. Can't wait to go back again!

My Wife and I celebrated our 2 year anniversary at this location .  We waited to go there specifically for a special occasion . We dressed up because when they first open they had a dress code . We got there to realized we were overdressed . There is absolutely no dress code .  While we had an okay waiter , we weren't the happiest because lets face it who wants to celebrate an intimate moment such as their anniversary sitting at the end of a sushi bar (where u cant even see the chef) watching waiters ring up orders all night....maybe some people but not us. We made a reservation and told them it was a special occasion, our 2 year anniversary, on the reservation, arrived 15 minutes early as well. We expressed to the hostess we didnt want to sit at the bar she explained to us that we had to reserve a table . I explained we did have a reservation  but she broke it down to me that we had to call to reserve a table . NO WHERE IS THAT LISTED ON THEIR WEBSITE !! ALL it says is reserve a table THATS IT. Ontop of that there were 4 empty tables when she decided to sit us at the bar .  Needless to say we werent big fans of our experience . AT ALL . MY wife and I are huge foodies we love to go out to eat and try alot on the menu. Normally, we stay at a restaurant at least hour ordering and trying things including desserts, we never just order 1 thing on the menu. We try it all normally spending over $100+. We only ordered 1 thing each and something to share(WHICH WE NEVER DO) and left . She does reviews of restaurants on ig and this experience wasnt worth giving any praise about due to lack of communication . My wife does not want to come back.  however 1 thing i did like about the restaurant was the lady sitting next to us . and she was a customer . The customer told us happy anniversary but none of the workers did . and we put it on our reservation !!!!  the food was okay . we left hungry . we still tipped our waiter because its not his fault.  i do not recommend this restaurant .
Very good!

Amazing vegan sushi, we ate far too much and I still didn't try even half of what I wanted to! Staff were very helpful and friendly and the food was well presented and incredibly tasty. Highly recommend the avocado maki, the flavours are incredible.
Really, really well prepared food. Was busy when we were there. The flavors are outstanding.

The food is top notch & would love to return but I don't like to be rushed. You are given 90" and then asked (nicely) to be on your way. We saw one family have to chow down their food - since they ordered a lot of dishes! We probably would have ordered more but it is not a place to really relax. Still, the food is definitely worth trying! Excellent vegan cuisine.
Really really fantastic! Not a vegan but I would eat this anytime! The textures and flavors were fantastic overall highly highly reccommend!

When meat-loving foodies can name a vegan restaurant one of their "favorites", that's a testimony to how great the flavors, textures, presentation and portions are. Another comment at our table was, "If you can tell me all vegan and plant-based food tastes like this, I could become a vegan." Yep. Good stuff.

A-M-A-Z-I-N-G. Everything I ate was incredible. All vegan, VERY gluten-free friendly (including all of their soy sauce, except the takeout packets so make sure to ask for a little container of the gf stuff if you get takeout or take home leftovers, I was bummed to discover this when I got back to my hotel).  Staff is friendly and very knowledgeable, my server gave me incredible recommendations. I am devastated to go home tomorrow and not have access to this place!  The sushi is pure art; actually replicating fresh fish sushi rather than the heavy tempura and spicy mayo alternatives I'm used to (which are also delicious but much easier to find and less refined).  I can't imagine that most omnivores wouldn't also love this food but especially if you're vegan or vegetarian, do yourself an enormous favor and try this place!
Absolutely amazing service and food.

(Translated by Google) It's the best vegan sushi ever! Really impressed since the first bite. All the dishes are not only delicious but elegant. We will definitely go again!  I completely subvert my impression of the vegetarian restaurant on the island! This is probably the first time I have eaten such [beauty] food, the atmosphere of the whole restaurant, the attitude of the waiter, the exquisiteness and deliciousness of the ingredients make us look back.  (Original) It's the best vegan sushi ever! Really impressed since the first bite. All the dishes are not only delicious but elegant. We will definitely go again!  完全顛覆我對於小島上素食餐廳的印象! 這大概也是我第一次吃到這麼[美]的食物，整個餐廳的氛圍，服務員的態度，食材的精緻和美味讓我們吮指回味。

The best vegan sushi EVER! I have never had anything like this before. We unfortunately don’t have any vegan sushi places in Sydney and so I was very excited to try Tane Vegan Izakaya on my small kauai trip while travelling through Hawaii. It was my top dining experience out of every place that I went to during my holiday. We got a seat at the bar, which I was initially concerned about as you do loose some intimacy but being right in front of the chefs was so much fun! They were so welcoming, friendly and had such a great energy, which kept us smiling throughout the night. We loved seeing them make the food and they offered us great suggestions! We ordered the Pacifica, sunset, baker, point Reyes as our rolls and the shizen shiitake and croquettes as our entrees. I can’t pick a favourite!
Amazing food!!! We will be back soon. I want to try everything in the menu.

Amazing Find in Honolulu!! Really impressed how authentic the vegan sushi tasted. Every roll we tried tasted absolutely delicious. Presentation was very artistic and can see how much care they took in it. We didn’t have a reservation but they were able to seat us by the sushi bar so reservation is recommended if you want a table.
Uniquely awesome!
A little expensive. Great vegan food. A little noisey (walls do not absorb noise good). Great fancy place to take a date.  Come early for free parking.
This place blew my mind, outstanding!!!
Really solid place.  Excellent sake menu.  I am not vegan and I really enjoyed the food and hospitality
Loved loved loved these creative amazing compassionate dishes!
Hard to believe everything was plant based, very good
First time trying vegan food and it was awesome!
Super good mushrooms and eggplant, hard to believe how good sushi can be without fish
Original food. Get your Vegan on.
Good food but a little pricy
Amazing! So worth it!!
Just had dinner here for the first time. Best Vegan Sushi Ever!!! Delicious cuisine with lots of choices. Staff was exceedingly friendly! Definitely would recommend this restaurant!!
Phenomenal food!
Best vegan food!! Period
The atmosphere is fantastic, service is great, and the food is delicious!
OMG....incredible beautiful food....awesome servers & staff!!!  Will be back for sure!!

Absolutely fantastic vegan food.  We travelled from Australia and decided on this place months before we came.  All the food exceeded expectations. Ramen, Gyozas & Sushi.  A must for vegans in Hawaii.

I always loved sushi and have been missing it since become vegan. This place amazed me with how excellent and real-tasting their vegan sushi was!! Service was ON POINT too. All they are missing is some #SpicyNinjaSauce 😜
Everything is vegan! Even the ice cream
This is a true @SpicyNinjaSauce kinda place, epic food!

Awesome. Better than you would imagine. The food is so artistic and worth much more than it's priced at. So delicious... And the people are so nice. Nika is an absolute star. You won't regret coming here, but it is very busy. Make a reservation.

Great food and awesome service! Food came out at a good pace, we ordered the speciality role 'the wedge' which was a deep fried sushi roll with tempura and some kind of Smoked tofu inside, it was so unique and delicious. My boyfriend is a huge meat eater and he also really enjoyed the food. Would definetely come back to try other dishes on the menu.
The. Best. Beautiful, delicious, well-made food! Everything we ate was fantastic!

A vegan restaurant open only for dinner serving Japanese themed food. Everything was Ala Carte. The food was made to share. We ordered a lot. With out drinks....it cost us about $25 per person.  The place was pretty full. Good to see that they are getting a lot of support from the community.  Hopefully, they will open for lunch service.  I think this place will make it.  This place is a bit noisey. The walls did not absorb the sound...so it is hard to have a conversation in a normal voice.  The service was great. Everyone was helping out without being over attentive.  The food was good.  I did not miss the meat.  Presentation was great.  Great bathrooms!  Handicap/wheel chair accessible.  Parking area shared with other businesses...but there is free street parking.

An absolute must for anyone, vegan or otherwise, when you're looking for an incredible upscale dining experience. The food is so flavorful and complex, and the service is impeccable. "Everyone should eat here!"

Had the Manila Dune, Sunset, Kailua and Pokai. Every dish was delicious. Loved the shredded tofu. The spicy tofu has the texture of tuna & mayonnaise. Seaweed pearls are like caviar but vegan. All dishes presented to a high standard. Shame it’s our last night, would have loved to visit again to try out more dishes. Best vegan restaurant we’ve visited in the Hawaii islands! 👍
Absolutely amazing! You'll never know it's vegan. Succulent flavors with beautiful presentation.
This pace is amazing....layers of flavors! Rather you eat meat or don’t - this place is an experience you have to try! You won’t be disappointed! Best vegan restaurant in Honolulu hands down!

This place is amazing for vegan/vegetarian person. It’s very reasonably price, food is amazing and fresh presentation is superb. Great little just at the curse of the city where there is no paying meters.. their dessert varies day today but this is what we got and it was amazing. We’re from California they do have another restaurant in San Francisco and if you look for vegan sushi it should pop up.
Amazing. Everything is so delicious.  Upscale, friendly staff, great vibe.

Outstanding Vegan Izakaya - among the best vegan restaurants currently in Honolulu.   Every dish we ordered was excellent.   High quality service, pleasant atmosphere and great food.   Will definitely go back.
The food is out of this world good. The first bite is heavenly. These guys could teach other sushi places a thing or two on service and quality food! EAT HERE!!

Classy, clean, consistently delicious. Their only downside is parking, but that’s not their fault. Oh and they don’t serve whiskey if that’s your thing (cuz it’s mine). Maybe one day...but I’ll continue to enjoy their many awesome options until then.
Best vegan sushi I've ever had. Loved the ambience, the service, and the food!
Truly delicious food. On any scale.
Extremely kind, great service, and delicious food!
An absolute food orgasm and such a pleasure being served by next-level smiling staff :-)

Best vegan restaurant on the island! Great customer service, perfect location, reasonable price, comfortable seating, delicious food.  It is a perfect place for couple, friends get together and family parties. I would highly recommend this restaurant. it's a 5-Star experience !  !
